This paper presents a linear least square solver that utilizes low precision TensorCore GPU, which is a topic related to numerical analysis (cs.NA) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses innovative algorithms and implementations, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper presents performance comparisons with other solvers, which could be related to scientific computing (cs.SC).
